{
  "texts": [
    "Then the four input channels are augmented by; adding Gaussian noise (applied with probability 0.5, zero mean and standard deviation uniformly sampled from [0.0, 0.05]), blurring the image (applied with probability 0.2, Gaussian blurring with standard deviation sampled from [0.5, 1.0]), faking lower resolution (zooming with a factor between 0.75 and 1.0 and then upsampling) and changing the gamma factor (scaling it with a factor between 0.8 and 1.2).",
    "Lastly the input image channels are normalized using Z-score normalization.",
    "Swin transformers.",
    "The Swin transformer segmentation network was implemented and trained using the MMSegmentation library 56.",
    "The architecture employed is the Swin-Base variant, as implemented in MMSegmentation, with a window size of 7 and a patch size of 4 × 4."
  ]
}